EDS definition from the journal EDS: "advances in data-driven methods to understand and predict environmental processes and impacts, and their patterns in space and time. The methodological scope is defined broadly to encompass artificial intelligence (including machine learning, deep learning, and computer vision), statistics, data mining, and econometrics, as well as hybrid approaches that combine data-driven methods with physical process-based modeling"
